{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a1967ec3-7e55-4e41-a960-0b51918ac797","content":"The issue is that **.NET MAUI Android expects the Microsoft Build of OpenJDK**, not Adoptium Temurin. Even though both are JDK 17, the .NET Android workload bundles its own JDK, and pointing `JAVA_HOME` to Temurin can cause build failures.\n\n**Fix — pick one:**\n\n1. **Let MAUI use its bundled JDK** (recommended):\n   ```bash\n   unset JAVA_HOME\n   ```\n   Remove any `JAVA_HOME` export from your `~/.zshrc` / `~/.bash_profile` as well.\n\n2. **Point to MAUI's JDK explicitly:**\n   ```bash\n   export JAVA_HOME=\"$(dotnet android javahome)\"\n   ```\n\n3. **Or set it per-project** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <JavaSdkDirectory>$(ANDROID_SDK_ROOT)/jdk</JavaSdkDirectory>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\nAfter changing, clean and rebuild:\n```bash\ndotnet clean && dotnet build -t:Run -f net8.0-android\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cb45adf9-7f80-488d-88db-478d20be1198","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is having a .NET MAUI Android build failure with a Java-related error on macOS. They have Adoptium Temurin JDK 17.0.12 installed with JAVA_HOME pointing to it.\n\nLet me think about what the common issue is here:\n\n.NET MAUI Android builds require a specific JDK version. Starting with .NET 8, MAUI/Android uses JDK 17. But there's a known issue specifically with **Adoptium Temurin** JDK on macOS related to the directory structure.\n\nOn macOS, the typical JAVA_HOME for Adoptium Temurin would be something like:\n\n\n`/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/temurin-17.jdk/Contents/Home`\n\nThe real problem is often that .NET's Android SDK tooling doesn't recognize Adoptium Temurin properly, or there's a version compatibility issue between what .NET expects and what Temurin provides. The most common culprits are JDK version mismatches—.NET 8 and 9 both require JDK 17, though some configurations might need JDK 11—or the fact that Microso